# STM32 BluePill LED/Switch Controller

## Project Description
Firmware for STM32F103C6T6 (Blue Pill) that controls GPIOB LEDs based on GPIOA switch inputs.

## Features
- Toggles all LEDs when any switch is pressed
- Hardware debouncing
- Efficient polling implementation

## Hardware Requirements
- STM32F103C6T6 (Blue Pill)
- 7x Tactile switches (GPIOA)
- 7x LEDs + 220Ω resistors (GPIOB)

## Pin Connections
| MCU Pin | Connection  |
|---------|-------------|
| PA0-PA6 | Switches to GND |
| PB3-PB9 | LED anodes |

## Build Instructions
1. Clone repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/STM32-BluePill-LED-Switch.git
   ```
2. Open with STM32CubeIDE
3. Build project (Project → Build All)
4. Flash to device

## Usage
1. Press any switch (PA0-PA6)
2. All LEDs (PB3-PB9) will toggle

